## ML vs Rule-Based Karar Agaci
```
├── Veri var mi (1000+ orneklem)? -> ML
│   ├── Tahmin/ongorusel? -> ML.NET regression/classification
│   ├── Anomali tespiti? -> ML.NET anomaly detection
│   ├── Text anlama? -> Semantic Kernel + LLM
│   └── Oneri sistemi? -> ML.NET recommendation
├── Veri az / kural net? -> Rule-based
│   ├── If/else yeterli? -> Business rules engine
│   └── Karar agaci? -> Decision table
└── Hibrit: Kural ile filtrele, ML ile sirala/skorla
```

## MLOps Lifecycle
```
1. Problem Definition -> Is problemi + basari kriteri tanimla
2. Data Collection    -> Veri kaynaklari + pipeline
3. Data Preparation   -> Temizlik, feature engineering
4. Model Training     -> ML.NET trainer secimi + cross-validation
5. Model Evaluation   -> Metrikler (RMSE, F1, AUC)
6. Model Registry     -> Versiyon + metadata kaydi
7. Deployment         -> API endpoint + A/B test
8. Monitoring         -> Data drift + model performance izleme
9. Retraining         -> Trigger-based (drift, schedule, manual)
```

## ML.NET Pipeline Pattern
```csharp
// Demand Forecast Pipeline
public class DemandForecastService
{
    public ITransformer TrainModel(IDataView trainingData)
    {
        var pipeline = _mlContext.Transforms
            .CopyColumns("Label", nameof(DemandData.Quantity))
            .Append(_mlContext.Transforms.Concatenate("Features",
                nameof(DemandData.DayOfWeek),
                nameof(DemandData.Month),
                nameof(DemandData.IsHoliday),
                nameof(DemandData.HistoricalAvg),
                nameof(DemandData.Trend)))
            .Append(_mlContext.Regression.Trainers.FastTree(
                numberOfLeaves: 20,
                numberOfTrees: 100,
                minimumExampleCountPerLeaf: 10));

        var model = pipeline.Fit(trainingData);
        
        // Cross-validation
        var cvResults = _mlContext.Regression.CrossValidate(trainingData, pipeline, numberOfFolds: 5);
        var avgRmse = cvResults.Average(r => r.Metrics.RootMeanSquaredError);
        _logger.LogInformation("Model trained. Avg RMSE: {Rmse}", avgRmse);
        
        return model;
    }

    public float Predict(DemandData input)
    {
        var engine = _mlContext.Model.CreatePredictionEngine<DemandData, DemandPrediction>(_model);
        return engine.Predict(input).PredictedQuantity;
    }
}
```

